1
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:27,660
♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 28]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:27,480
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:33,120
Why does it
have to be Huntington's Disease?

19
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:35,920
You should know

20
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,680
that global research on it
has come to a standstill.

21
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,360
The significance of the topic

22
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,680
has been detailed

23
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,360
in the project proposal.

24
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,120
Director Du, I hope you can

25
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,960
read it as soon as possible
and stamp it officially.

26
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,360
I won't agree.

27
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,160
Wait, why?

28
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:58,560
As a doctor,
I tackle research challenges.

29
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,760
As a director,

30
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:01,560
shouldn't you support and encourage it?

31
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,320
If you study chorea,

32
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,160
how can you publish papers?

33
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,960
How can you get a title?

34
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,880
And you don't want

35
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:11,320
to retire
without ever being a full professor,

36
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:12,520
watching your juniors

37
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,960
surpass you one by one, right?

38
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,720
You're indeed a good director.

39
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,760
Your perspective on the issue

40
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,480
is truly insightful,

41
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,080
but these concerns have never been

42
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,240
within my consideration.

43
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:30,560
Yunzheng.

44
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,040
It's not the time for us to argue.

45
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,520
I have intercepted

46
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,160
your request
to change the research topic

47
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,760
and also the project proposal.

48
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,360
I'll give you a few days

49
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,160
to withdraw them quickly.

50
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:03,100
[Outpatient, Zhang He Hospital]

51
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,440
Come in, please.

52
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,760
You wanted to see me, Prof. Wen?

53
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:19,640
Yes.

54
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,560
I've researched

55
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,920
Huntington's Disease for most of my life

56
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,360
and gathered these research materials

57
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,840
and work notes.

58
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,480
Now that I'm retiring,

59
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:32,680
I want

60
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,040
to give them all to you.

61
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,200
To me?

62
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,760
I heard

63
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,760
that you carry the pathogenic gene, too.

64
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,640
Yeah.

65
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,960
For public and private reasons,

66
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,640
these research materials

67
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,280
will be helpful to you.

68
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,440
Apart from the part
involving patient privacy

69
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,160
that cannot be shared,

70
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:58,160
all the detours I encountered
during the research

71
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,880
are in it.

72
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,840
Next,

73
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,960
you must continue to work hard,

74
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,760
and I hope you can beat the clock.

75
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:17,760
We'll do our best.

76
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:34,380
[Outpatient]

77
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,160
I don't understand.

78
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:38,320
Why did Dr. Gu suddenly
change his research topic?

79
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,280
His previous glioma topic,

80
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,320
if continued,

81
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,080
would have no shortage
of papers and funding.

82
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,840
Why did he suddenly give it up?

83
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,280
I think Dr. Gu

84
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,400
is too clever.

85
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,520
Having published many papers,

86
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:49,520
he became proud.

87
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:50,960
Having several high-score articles,

88
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,320
he began to swell with pride,

89
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:54,080
thinking that with his own power,

90
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,880
he could overturn
the world's research results.

91
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:57,320
Do you think it's possible?

92
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,920
Could it be because of Su Wei'an?

93
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,560
Her aunt carries the gene.

94
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,280
Wen Ran previously said
that she does, too.

95
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,360
No one's worth it.

96
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,320
I didn't realize Dr. Gu

97
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,760
was so infatuated.

98
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,400
Why is it that I was the only one
who didn't know

99
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,600
about your change in research topic?

100
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,920
When did it happen?

101
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,720
Wei'an.

102
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,000
Answer me first.

103
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,040
I can't

104
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,600
stay in this room anymore today.

105
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,160
Why is everyone who comes in

106
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:37,400
so excited?

107
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,200
No, Gu Yunzheng.

108
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,080
You've been studying glioma for so long.

109
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,720
Don't you feel bad
about giving it to someone else?

110
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,320
I believe Mr. Wang

111
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,600
will find the right person
to take it over.

112
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,160
No matter who does it,

113
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,000
it's for the advancement of medicine.

114
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
I'm not focused on glioma now.

115
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,960
Even if I continue,

116
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,200
it will backfire.

117
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,720
This is what

118
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,160
I got from Prof. Wen just now.

119
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,120
It's all the roadblocks he encountered

120
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,600
in researching chorea
for half of his life.

121
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,200
Even a senior like Prof. Wen

122
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,680
couldn't do it.

123
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,800
Why do you think

124
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,000
we can make progress from scratch?

125
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,600
Wei'an.

126
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,440
What I want to do is not just

127
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,360
simply make progress,

128
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:30,200
not to alleviate chorea,

129
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,800
nor to delay the disease process,

130
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,560
but

131
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,600
to find a cure for Huntington's Disease.

132
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,440
I know

133
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,960
it does sound impossible,

134
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,040
but I want to try.

135
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,000
Try what?

136
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,680
That's how my life will be.

137
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,120
I don't care anymore.

138
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,000
But you're different.

139
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,400
Your prime in your research career

140
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,600
has just begun.

141
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,480
You don't care?

142
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,000
Why would you think that?

143
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:13,880
Gu Yunzheng.

144
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,000
We must admit the fact

145
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,080
that Huntington's Disease

146
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,200
is an incurable disease.

147
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,000
Even if we try our best,

148
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,400
the chance of finding a cure is likely

149
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,520
less than one in a million.

150
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,120
Regardless of encountering

151
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,320
obstacles or failures in my experiments,

152
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,000
it doesn't matter

153
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,320
because I'm trying to save myself.

154
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,960
But you're different.

155
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,240
You've got a good foundation

156
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,720
in glioma.

157
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,400
You'll probably be an influential expert

158
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,680
in the future.

159
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,280
I don't want you to make

160
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,880
such unnecessary sacrifices for me.

161
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,800
I also don't want you

162
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,000
to live every day

163
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,720
in a vague hope like me.

164
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,080
Why is it an unnecessary sacrifice?

165
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,040
And why is it a vague hope?

166
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,320
Isn't it?

167
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,880
Su Wei'an.

168
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:24,000
From the moment I started
the Huntington's Disease project,

169
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,800
I've reviewed nearly a hundred papers.

170
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,520
I know it's difficult.

171
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,320
But with each step I took,

172
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,400
I believe it was feasible.

173
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,550
I even have a plan

174
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:36,880
for the next five or ten years.

175
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,790
Are these,

176
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,600
in your mind,

177
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,150
just short-sighted decisions?

178
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,400
Why can't you

179
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,080
just stay with me on this path?

180
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,360
I just don't want you

181
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,160
to become blind for love.

182
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,720
And I don't want you to sacrifice

183
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,520
the achievements you deserve.

184
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:07,960
Even you think

185
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,360
I'm blinded by love.

186
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,040
Right?

187
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,440
Yes, Su Wei'an.

188
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,400
It's you.

189
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,640
You made the research
of Huntington's Disease more than

190
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,960
just a complicated experiment for me.

191
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,960
I admit that's true.

192
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,920
But I found deeper conviction

193
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,480
in every annotation

194
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,560
I wrote in the book,

195
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,400
every cell I cultivated,

196
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,600
and every fluorescence staining I made

197
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,320
because of you.

198
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:41,360
But it's not just because of you.

199
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,320
It's also because of every patient

200
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,000
suffering from Huntington's Disease.

201
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,200
Someone has to start it,

202
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,320
and someone has to pave the way.

203
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,400
Su Wei'an.

204
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,400
Where has your faith gone?

205
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,520
Living every day with the belief
of curing Huntington's Disease

206
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,480
only makes me disappointed.

207
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,080
Then,

208
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,880
let me shoulder

209
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:35,960
all the disappointment.

210
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,560
All you need to do

211
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,880
is to believe in me.

212
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,800
I'm not afraid of anything.

213
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,320
I'm just afraid
that you'll suddenly give up.

214
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,120
Since I've returned to the lab,

215
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,920
I won't easily give up.

216
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,680
But this shouldn't

217
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:13,560
mix up our futures together.

218
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,480
I think we both need some time

219
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,400
to calmly think things through.

220
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,800
I'll stay at home tonight.

221
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,160
(Su Wei'an)

222
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,120
(Do you not believe
in my research ability)

223
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,080
(or my determination to do this?)

224
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,400
(Anyway,)

225
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:40,120
(I won't give up.)

226
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:11,860
[Experiment Supplies Procurement List]

227
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:19,720
Jiang, why are you here?

228
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:20,840
Look.

229
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,480
I lined up to buy this for you,

230
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,560
the internet-famous Napoleon Cake.

231
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,320
Thanks.

232
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,920
You've been working late these days.

233
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,560
I'm asleep when you get home.

234
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,200
I'm awake, but you're gone.

235
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:33,480
I haven't seen my boyfriend
for a long time.

236
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,480
Now I'm here with you.

237
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,400
Thanks.

238
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,320
Come back.

239
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,360
What's up?

240
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,160
Anything else?

241
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:42,960
Let's go to the cafeteria.

242
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:44,960
I'll leave after you finish eating.

243
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,000
I can't.

244
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,600
The patients are waiting for me.

245
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,800
I have to hurry back.

246
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,200
I'll stay with you next time, Jiang.

247
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:50,920
I'm sorry.

248
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,400
Next time, I promise.

249
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,120
Come back.

250
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,280
Fang Mingfan!

251
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,880
I've found

252
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:04,320
that men are fickle creatures.

253
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,240
Forever

254
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,840
is just a lie.

255
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,800
What happened again?

256
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,600
Fang Mingfan hasn't been with me
for a long time,

257
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:15,440
leaving home early and returning late,

258
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:17,400
and he replies slowly to messages, too.

259
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:20,240
Moving into his place
has been nothing but lonely.

260
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,760
We see each other less
than roommates living together.

261
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,760
A surgeon is very busy.

262
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:31,200
You've been staring at that screen

263
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:31,960
since you arrived.

264
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,040
So?

265
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,760
Have I wasted your working time?

266
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:35,600
Alright.

267
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,560
I'm sorry.

268
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,720
I shouldn't have been on the computer

269
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:39,560
during our date.

270
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,840
Go ahead.

271
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,640
Wei'an.

272
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,320
You guys all have jobs.

273
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:45,040
Only I am unemployed.

274
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:46,160
You have no idea

275
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:47,400
how many people envy your life.

276
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:48,960
Enjoy a carefree life

277
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:51,640
without the pressure of making a living.

278
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,640
But for Fang Mingfan,

279
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,920
I bet

280
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:59,200
he definitely didn't mean to ignore you.

281
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,760
It's just that sometimes

282
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,200
he's really busy with work.

283
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,160
He's overwhelmed.

284
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,960
Don't you have a date with Dr. Gu today?

285
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,520
No need to work overtime in the lab?

286
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,240
What's wrong?

287
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,600
Did you have a fight with him?

288
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,320
Did he make you angry?

289
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,400
Wei'an.

290
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,720
Let's have fun this weekend.

291
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:37,920
Two days and one night.

292
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,720
I know of a nice inn.

293
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,280
But I have to read a few papers
this weekend.

294
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:43,880
Come on, it's the weekend.

295
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,400
Don't waste it to read papers.

296
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,320
And it's been a long time

297
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,080
since we went out together.

298
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:49,720
Please.

299
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:51,920
Okay.

300
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:52,680
Good.

301
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:09,920
Look at that mountain.

302
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:10,920
It's so beautiful.

303
00:17:14,830 --> 00:17:16,070
Hey, puppy.

304
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:20,880
Let's go.

305
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,200
Bye.

306
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:29,720
Hello.

307
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,600
I've booked a mountain-view room
with a king-size bed.

308
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,320
You see.

309
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,440
Alright, little lady.

310
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:35,280
Wait a moment.

311
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,160
Hi.

312
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,120
What a small world.

313
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,040
What are you doing here?

314
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,040
Jiang.

315
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,640
I'm sorry

316
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:53,320
for ignoring you recently.

317
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:55,480
I'll be with you wholeheartedly
this weekend.

318
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,040
Don't be mad at me.

319
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,040
Thank you.

320
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:01,760
I'll leave her to you.

321
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:02,680
Take good care of her.

322
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:03,840
Yes, ma'am.

323
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:19,720
What are you doing here?

324
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,800
If I said it was a chance encounter,

325
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:24,080
would you believe me?

326
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:26,760
No.

327
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,160
I haven't seen you after work.

328
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,360
You didn't reply to my messages either,

329
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:33,960
so I followed you here.

330
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:37,680
Let me help you.

331
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:38,160
No need.

332
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:46,360
Su Wei'an.

333
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:48,920
You

334
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,600
look really beautiful today.

335
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,280
Go back to your room.

336
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,320
Jiang.

337
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,440
I've got a lot of surprises for you.

338
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:28,240
Why don't you come with me?

339
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:29,400
What surprises?

340
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,360
You'll find out when we get there.

341
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:36,000
Fang Mingfan.

342
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,880
This isn't your plan, is it?

343
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:42,880
I was trying to set you two up.

344
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,160
But you betrayed me pretty quickly.

345
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,640
Let me clarify.

346
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,400
I didn't conspire with Fang Mingfan.

347
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:52,600
He prepared the surprises
for Jiang Muying.

348
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:54,000
It has nothing to do with me.

349
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,440
That's right, Wei'an.

350
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,400
Why don't you join us?

351
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,200
I don't mind if you're the third wheel.

352
00:19:59,200 --> 00:19:59,840
I do.

353
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:04,640
Fang Mingfan.

354
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,640
If you disappoint me this time,

355
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:08,800
you're done.

356
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:11,160
I won't.

357
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,720
Let's go.

358
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:14,200
Let's go and have a look.

359
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,560
Drink some water.

360
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,080
Fang Mingfan.

361
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,120
Where are you taking me?

362
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,720
I read online

363
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:40,240
it's where we can see
the most beautiful sunset.

364
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,320
We'll just go there and wait.

365
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:45,240
Sitting there and waiting
for the sunset is enough.

366
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:48,880
How far is it?

367
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,240
We're almost there.

368
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,240
Come on, Jiang.

369
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,400
Jiang.

370
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,400
Let's go there.

371
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,680
Come on.

372
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:09,720
Hurry up.

373
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,000
When will we get there?

374
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,160
We'll be there soon.

375
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:19,720
It must be here, right?

376
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,160
I can't walk anymore.

377
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,560
Jiang.

378
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:29,360
Fang Mingfan.

379
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:31,760
There are so many trees
blocking the view.

380
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:33,200
How can we see the sunset?

381
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:35,080
Am I mistaken?

382
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:36,240
Jiang.

383
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,800
Do you have the strength
to walk a little more?

384
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:43,200
You...

385
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,480
Come on.

386
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,720
We're almost there.

387
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,680
Come on.

388
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,040
Fang Mingfan.

389
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:55,720
Slow down.

390
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:56,800
Slow down, Jiang.

391
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,520
We're finally here.

392
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,040
What's wrong with you?

393
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:06,640
Didn't we come to see the sunset?

394
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,640
Why did you bring me here?

395
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:10,200
Jiang.

396
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,040
Have you watched the movie
"My Sassy Girl"?

397
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,440
Let's bury a time capsule here, too.

398
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,200
We can dig it up when we get old.

399
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,320
It will definitely make us happy.

400
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,040
Dig deeper.

401
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:40,840
It's so big.

402
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:41,840
Okay.

403
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:44,920
Fang Mingfan.

404
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,800
What's this? Hurry up!

405
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:48,720
Catch it!

406
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:50,080
Fang Mingfan.

407
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,720
You threw it at me.

408
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:52,800
It's okay.

409
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,000
Where is it?

410
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,200
It's gone.

411
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,000
It's just an earthworm.

412
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,680
You threw it at me, Fang Mingfan.

413
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:05,760
No, Jiang.

414
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:06,880
I threw it this way.

415
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:10,880
I didn't know you were going this way.

416
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,000
It wasn't intentional.

417
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,360
Dig it yourself.

418
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:19,720
Jiang.

419
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,040
Wei'an.

420
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:31,440
Where are you going?

421
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,600
Back to the inn.

422
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,400
Where's Fang Mingfan?

423
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,040
Where's Dr. Gu?

424
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,200
Why aren't you together?

425
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,600
I don't know what to say.

426
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:49,120
Wei'an.

427
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:53,320
Why can't you try to understand him?

428
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:54,960
How should I understand him?

429
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:58,560
You know Huntington's Disease

430
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:01,200
is a lifelong research challenge.

431
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:04,800
His life will be ruined because of me.

432
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,280
Why do you shoulder

433
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,760
all the responsibility on yourself?

434
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,960
Even if his life is ruined,

435
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:14,120
it's his own choice.

436
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,160
If it wasn't for me,

437
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,440
he wouldn't have researched
Huntington's Disease.

438
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:21,160
I can't be so selfish.

439
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:22,880
I can't let him ruin his life

440
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:25,600
and career because of me.

441
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,160
The way you are pushing him away now

442
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,440
is truly selfish.

443
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:31,160
Aren't you just afraid of being blamed?

444
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:32,640
Have you ever thought about

445
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:34,840
how difficult it is for Dr. Gu
to choose this path?

446
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,800
You're just going against him

447
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,040
like everyone else.

448
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:39,880
Hasn't he heard enough of that?

449
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,120
Jiang.

450
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,360
I finally found you.

451
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:53,560
Jiang.

452
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:55,360
There's another good place
I haven't taken you yet.

453
00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:56,800
There definitely
won't be any earthworms.

454
00:24:58,280 --> 00:24:59,080
Wei'an.

455
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,560
Could you give me a chance to explain?

456
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,640
Where are you taking me?

457
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:07,920
Come on, hurry up.

458
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,080
Wei'an.

459
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,480
I also want to take you somewhere.

460
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:40,200
Jiang.

461
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:42,240
I heard this bridge is magical.

462
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,240
As long as they write the names

463
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,880
of the couple on it and hang it up,

464
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:49,160
their love will last forever,
and they'll grow old together.

465
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,280
Who wants to grow old with you?

466
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:56,800
It's okay to hang it up for peace.

467
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,240
I'll put our card

468
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:04,520
right in the middle.

469
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,440
Anyone who passes by will see it,

470
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,560
and they'll give us their blessing.

471
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:09,480
Be careful.

472
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,280
Are you done?

473
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,440
Done.

474
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:19,440
Come down!

475
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,560
Come down!

476
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:28,440
I love Jiang Muying.

477
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:30,960
Our love is the best in the world.

478
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,360
Who is it?

479
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:42,480
This is mine!

480
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,920
Who knocked it down?

481
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:45,360
It was you two, right?

482
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,760
You only care about your love?

483
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:49,040
I'm 40 years old and still not married.

484
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,200
Don't I deserve love?

485
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:50,920
Wait.

486
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:51,760
Run.

487
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,400
Run.

488
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:56,640
Stop.

489
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:58,760
Stop right there!

490
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:03,620
[Jiang Muying & Fang Mingfan:
Our love is the best in the world.]

491
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,760
Does he chase after us?

492
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:10,920
No.

493
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,520
Look at what you've done.

494
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,520
I'm exhausted.

495
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:26,760
I'm sorry, Jiang.

496
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,960
I actually planned a lot of surprises.

497
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:30,880
But I messed them all up.

498
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:35,160
You get wronged at home

499
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,920
and even when we travel.

500
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:40,120
I'm not a good boyfriend.

501
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,160
I'm useless.

502
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,320
Well, at least our love

503
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,360
is the best in the world now.

504
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,280
So, you've forgiven me?

505
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:04,800
I've got your heart.

506
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:08,600
That's great, Jiang.

507
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:13,560
You're so sweet.

508
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:15,680
Sure.

509
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:33,360
Wei'an.

510
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,200
Do you know the origin of Dujiangyan?

511
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,640
Over 2,000 years ago,

512
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,000
the Shu Plain

513
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:48,800
was suffering from drought in the east
and flood in the west

514
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,440
due to its narrow river channels.

515
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,400
But Li Bing and his son

516
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,600
created a miracle

517
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:58,000
and built
the Dujiangyan Irrigation System.

518
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,320
Did you bring me here

519
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:10,240
to tell me about this part
of history learned in middle school?

520
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:14,360
We all used to think that

521
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,920
"Yu Gong Moves Mountains" is a myth.

522
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:20,880
However,

523
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:23,400
Li Bing and his son

524
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,920
used fire to burn the rocks,

525
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:28,000
then cooled them with water.

526
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,600
They used the principle
of thermal expansion and contraction

527
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:32,200
to bore through the mountains

528
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,440
and create the Baopingkou.

529
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,960
I know you're trying
to tell me something

530
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:40,160
about how people can overcome nature.

531
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,400
But how many Dujiangyans are there
in the history?

532
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,840
And how many Li Bings are there?

533
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,880
There are not so many miracles
in the world.

534
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,800
Even if no miracle happens,

535
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:57,800
I might fail

536
00:29:58,320 --> 00:29:59,960
to develop an effective medicine

537
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:03,400
and be just an associate professor
in my lifetime.

538
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,560
You might leave me,

539
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:08,800
and I might grow old alone.

540
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,080
The worst scenario

541
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,240
could just be this.

542
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,280
Gu Yunzheng.

543
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:23,640
It's enough for me

544
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:25,640
to walk the tough road alone.

545
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,320
You don't have
to get involved in this mess.

546
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:32,800
Since someone has to wade through it,

547
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,680
why can't I join?

548
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,440
As a doctor,

549
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,480
I know better than anyone

550
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:43,520
what it's really like to be
in this world.

551
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:46,760
All we can do

552
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,600
is to keep our own pace.

553
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,560
Every step we take

554
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:54,200
brings us closer to victory.

555
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:05,520
In the history of mankind,

556
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,120
those 2,000 years

557
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,120
are just a moment.

558
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:12,840
Joy

559
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:14,400
or sadness,

560
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,360
it all passes in the blink of an eye.

561
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:19,320
Wei'an.

562
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,600
Let's stop wasting our time

563
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:23,280
on neglecting each other,

564
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:24,400
okay?

565
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,040
Even though

566
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,600
it's kind of fun

567
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:35,400
watching you lose your temper.

568
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:41,360
What does this have to do
with Dujiangyan?

569
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:44,560
Split the water in sixty-forty,
the sand in twenty-eighty.

570
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:48,600
Even if your emotions erupt
like a flash flood,

571
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,440
they can be resolved

572
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,120
when they come to me,

573
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:54,720
turning danger into safety.

574
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:57,200
Who taught you that?

575
00:31:58,240 --> 00:32:00,680
